olive oil
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet beef mince
1 packet tomato paste
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 tomato
1 Kumara
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
½ tbs water (for the onion)
½ cup water (for the beef)
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the
boil.
• Peel kumara and cut into bite-sized chunks.
• Cook kumara in the boiling water until easily
pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and
return kumara to the pan.
• Add the butter, milk and Aussie spice blend,
then mash until smooth.

Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help
mash the kumara!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice onion. Grate the carrot.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook onion, stirring,
until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Add the balsamic
vinegar, water (for the onion) and the brown
sugar and mix well. Cook until dark and sticky,
3-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef mince
and carrot, breaking the mince up with a spoon,
until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add All-American spice blend and tomato
paste and cook, stirring, until fragrant,
1-2 minutes.
• Add water (for the beef) and cook until
slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes. Stir through
caramelised onion and season to taste.

• Preheat grill to medium-high. Transfer beef
filling to a baking dish and evenly spread with
the kumara mash.
• Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese. Grill
until lightly golden, 5-8 minutes.

Little cooks: Join in on the fun by smoothing the
mash mixture evenly over the pie!

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato. In a medium
bowl, combine a drizzle of white wine vinegar
and olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.
• Add salad leaves and tomato. Toss to coat.

Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salad!

• Divide All-American beef and caramelised onion
pie between plates.
• Serve with tomato salad. Enjoy!